"""
tests/test_scoring_engine_contract.py
================================================================================
Scoring Engine Contract Tests — v2.1.0
================================================================================

Why this revision (v2.1.0 vs v2.0.0)
-------------------------------------
- FIX: `test_scoring_all_exports` now checks every name in `scoring.__all__`,
    not just a subset. v2.0.0 missed `assign_rank_overall`,
    `ForecastParameters`, `ScoringEngine`, `DEFAULT_FORECASTS`, `score_quote`,
    `ScoringWeights`, `__version__`.
- FIX: Added `test_score_quote_alias` — actual scoring.py exposes THREE
    aliases (compute_scores / score_row / score_quote) but v2.0.0 only
    tested score_row.
- FIX: Added `test_scoring_weights_alias` — documented compat alias
    `ScoringWeights = ScoreWeights` was unchecked.
- FIX: Added `test_default_forecasts_instantiable` — `DEFAULT_FORECASTS` is
    exported from `__all__` but v2.0.0 never exercised it.
- FIX: Added `test_asset_scores_to_dict_returns_all_fields` — v2.0.0's
    check only verified 3 keys out of 30+, letting silent field deletion
    regressions through.
- FIX: Added `test_overall_score_raw_bounds` and
    `test_overall_penalty_factor_bounds` — v2.0.0 tested float-ness via
    SCORE_FLOAT_FIELDS but never the semantic bounds. `overall_score_raw`
    must be in [0, 100], `overall_penalty_factor` must be in [0, 1].
- FIX: Added `test_compute_scores_does_not_mutate_input` — defensive
    check that `compute_scores({...})` doesn't touch the caller's dict.
- FIX: Added `test_score_and_rank_rows_does_not_mutate_input_by_default`
    — `score_and_rank_rows` defaults to `inplace=False`; verify it.
- 🔑 FIX CORRECTNESS: `test_rank_rows_by_overall_ordering` (renamed to
    `test_rank_rows_by_overall_assigns_rank_field`) in v2.0.0 asserted
    that the output list was sorted descending. But scoring.py v2.2.0's
    actual implementation preserves input order and only assigns
    `rank_overall` to each row. The v2.0.0 test would fail against the
    real scoring module. v2.1.0 rewrites it to verify the correct
    contract: order preserved, rank_overall reflects sorted-desc position.
- 🔑 FIX CORRECTNESS: `test_assign_rank_overall_adds_rank` in v2.0.0 used
    `enumerate(ranked, start=1)` and asserted `rank_overall == idx`,
    which only holds if the input is already sorted desc. But
    `_make_rows(3)` produces ascending scores (0, 10, 20), so position-0
    gets rank 3 (lowest), not rank 1. v2.1.0 fixes the assertion to
    match the actual score-to-rank mapping.
- FIX: Added `test_assign_rank_overall_rank_contiguous` — verifies that
    assigned ranks form a contiguous {1..N} set with no duplicates/gaps.
- FIX: Added `test_assign_rank_overall_inplace_false_copies` — v2.0.0
    only tested the default `inplace=True` path.
- FIX: Added `test_scoring_engine_enrich_with_scores` — the engine
    wrapper exposes BOTH `compute_scores` and `enrich_with_scores`;
    v2.0.0 only tested the first.
- FIX: Added `test_rank_rows_by_overall_empty_input` — empty-list edge
    case for the standalone ranker (v2.0.0 only tested
    `score_and_rank_rows([])`).
- FIX: Added `test_expected_return_fields_are_fractions` — covers
    `expected_return_1m/3m/12m` (same shape as `expected_roi_*`) which
    v2.0.0 missed.
- FIX: Dead imports removed (`inspect`, `Sequence`).

What this test suite enforces (scope unchanged from v2.0.0)
------------------------------------------------------------
1) scoring module is importable from the expected paths
2) SCORING_VERSION / __version__ present and semver-shaped
3) compute_scores / score_row / score_quote / enrich_with_scores callable
4) AssetScores dataclass has all required fields
5) ScoreWeights dataclass has correct default weights (sum == 1.0)
6) ForecastParameters dataclass is importable + DEFAULT_FORECASTS instantiable
7) ScoringEngine wrapper is callable (compute_scores + enrich_with_scores)
8) Recommendation vocabulary is canonical
   (STRONG_BUY/BUY/HOLD/REDUCE/SELL; STRONG_SELL allowed but not emitted)
9) Risk bucket vocabulary is canonical (Low/Moderate/High)
10) Confidence bucket vocabulary is canonical (Low/Medium/High)
11) Score output fields are float in [0, 100] when present
12) overall_penalty_factor is a fraction in [0, 1]
13) Expected ROI fields are fractions (abs <= 1.5)
14) Deterministic: same input → same output
15) compute_scores does NOT mutate its input dict
16) Sparse row: does not raise, returns sensible defaults
17) Rich row: all score fields populated
18) rank_rows_by_overall / assign_rank_overall: correct ordering (+ inplace=False)
19) score_and_rank_rows: end-to-end list scoring + rank_overall contiguous

Design goals (preserved from v2.0.0)
- No network calls.
- No FastAPI / async test infrastructure needed.
- Compatible with plain pytest.
- Import-safe: falls back gracefully when scoring module lives at different paths.
- Uses the v2.x project scoring.py API (compute_scores returns dict).
"""
